---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Privacy Policy — NomsAI"
  description="NomsAI privacy policy. Your food logs never leave your device. No account required, no data harvesting. Last updated 19 March 2026."
>

  <article class="py-16 sm:py-24 bg-[#f4f2ef] dark:bg-[#0a0a0a]">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">

      <!-- Header -->
      <header class="mb-12">
        <p class="text-sm font-bold uppercase tracking-widest mb-3" style="color:#c8920a">Legal</p>
        <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-[#1c1714] dark:text-white mb-3">Privacy Policy</h1>
        <p style="color:#6b6560">Last updated: 19 March 2026 · NomsAI by a solo developer</p>

        <!-- Callout — the short version -->
        <div class="mt-8 rounded-2xl p-6 border-l-4" style="background:#edeae5;border-color:#c8920a">
          <p class="font-semibold text-[#1c1714] dark:text-white mb-1">The short version:</p>
          <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed" style="color:#6b6560">
            Your food logs, workout logs, weight data, and calorie goals never leave your device. We don't store them, we can't see them, and they disappear if you uninstall the app. The only data on our server is a random ID and your credit balance — none of which identifies you.
          </p>
        </div>
      </header>

      <!-- Content -->
      <div class="prose-legal">

        <h2>1. Who We Are</h2>
        <p>NomsAI is a minimalist calorie-tracking app built and operated by a solo developer based in the United Kingdom. References to "we", "us", or "our" mean that developer, acting as data controller under the UK GDPR and EU GDPR. For questions or data requests, contact <a href="mailto:privacy@nomsai.app">privacy@nomsai.app</a>.</p>

        <h2>2. No Account Required</h2>
        <p>NomsAI does not require you to create an account or provide any personal information such as your name, email address, or date of birth. When you first open the app, a random UUID (e.g. <code>a3f8…</code>) is generated on your device. This is your only identifier. We have no way to link it to you as a person.</p>

        <h2>3. What We Collect</h2>
        <p>The following data is stored on our server, associated only with your anonymous Device ID:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Device ID</strong> — A randomly generated UUID created on your device at first launch. Pseudonymous: we cannot identify you from it alone.</li>
          <li><strong>Credit balance and Supporter Pass status</strong> — Whether you have an active Supporter Pass or purchased log credits. Necessary to deliver the service.</li>
          <li><strong>Last session timestamp</strong> — The date and time you last opened the app. Used solely to compute aggregate retention metrics. Never shared externally.</li>
          <li><strong>Daily AI usage counter (Supporter Pass holders only)</strong> — A count of AI requests made today. Used solely to enforce a daily fair-use limit. Resets automatically each day.</li>
          <li><strong>Purchase transaction IDs</strong> — When you purchase credits or a Supporter Pass, the App Store or Google Play transaction ID is stored alongside your Device ID. Used solely to prevent duplicate crediting. Auto-deleted after 2 years.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>We do <strong>not</strong> collect your name, email, location, contacts, camera, microphone, passwords, payment card details, or <strong>any food, dietary, or health information</strong>.</p>

        <h2>4. What Stays on Your Device</h2>
        <p>The following data is stored exclusively in your app's local storage and <strong>never sent to our server</strong>:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Food logs</strong> — AI-extracted items, macro estimates, and timestamps.</li>
          <li><strong>Workout logs</strong> — Activity type, duration, and estimated calories burned.</li>
          <li><strong>Weight entries</strong> — Body weight measurements, dates, and your weekly weight-change target.</li>
          <li><strong>Calorie and macro goals</strong> — Your target calories, protein, carbs, and fat.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>Your original free-text input (e.g. "2 eggs and toast") is sent to our AI provider to estimate macros and is then discarded. It is not saved anywhere — not on our server, not on your device.</p>
        <p>If you uninstall the app or switch to a new phone, your log history, goals, and weight entries are gone. We have no copy and no way to restore them.</p>

        <h2>5. How We Use Your Data and Our Lawful Basis</h2>
        <p>We process your data under UK GDPR Article 6. We do <strong>not</strong> sell, rent, share, or use your data for advertising. We do <strong>not</strong> use your data to train AI models.</p>

        <h2>6. Third-Party Services</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Google Gemini API</strong> (United States) — Your food-entry text is sent to estimate macros. Only the text is sent; your Device ID is never shared with Google. Transfer covered by Standard Contractual Clauses.</li>
          <li><strong>RevenueCat</strong> (United States) — Manages in-app purchases. Receives your Device ID (anonymous) and purchase receipt. Transfer covered by Standard Contractual Clauses.</li>
          <li><strong>Apple App Store / Google Play</strong> — Process payments. We never see your payment details.</li>
          <li><strong>MongoDB Atlas</strong> (European Union) — Stores server-side data (Device ID, credits, last-session timestamp) on SOC 2 Type II certified infrastructure. Data remains within the EU.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>7. Data Retention</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Food & workout logs</strong> — Device only. Auto-pruned after 365 days. Deleted when you uninstall.</li>
          <li><strong>Weight entries</strong> — Device only. Auto-pruned after 2 years. Deleted when you uninstall.</li>
          <li><strong>Server data</strong> — Retained until you delete your account via Settings → Delete Account.</li>
          <li><strong>Purchase transaction IDs</strong> — Auto-deleted after 2 years, or immediately on account deletion.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>8. Medical Disclaimer</h2>
        <p>NomsAI is an informational macro-tracking tool, not a medical device. It does not provide medical, clinical, or dietary advice. Do not use it to manage any medical condition. Always consult a qualified healthcare professional before making health decisions.</p>

        <h2>9. Your Rights (GDPR / UK GDPR)</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Access & portability</strong> — Use Settings → Export My Data.</li>
          <li><strong>Erasure</strong> — Settings → Delete Account removes all server-side data instantly.</li>
          <li><strong>Rectification</strong> — We hold no personal data that could be inaccurate.</li>
          <li><strong>Object to legitimate-interests processing</strong> — Contact <a href="mailto:privacy@nomsai.app">privacy@nomsai.app</a>.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>10. Right to Lodge a Complaint</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>UK:</strong> Information Commissioner's Office — <a href="https://ico.org.uk/make-a-complaint/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">ico.org.uk/make-a-complaint</a></li>
          <li><strong>EEA:</strong> Your national Data Protection Authority — <a href="https://edpb.europa.eu/about-edpb/about-edpb/members_en" target="_blank" rel="noopener">edpb.europa.eu</a></li>
        </ul>

        <h2>11. Children</h2>
        <p>NomsAI is not directed at children under 13 (under 16 in the EEA). The app is rated 17+ on the App Store.</p>

        <h2>12. California Residents (CCPA)</h2>
        <p>We do not sell, rent, or share your personal information. To exercise any CCPA rights, contact <a href="mailto:privacy@nomsai.app">privacy@nomsai.app</a> with your Device ID (visible in Settings).</p>

        <h2>13. Changes to This Policy</h2>
        <p>The "last updated" date at the top will change when we update this policy. Continued use of the app after changes constitutes acceptance.</p>

        <h2>14. Contact</h2>
        <p><a href="mailto:privacy@nomsai.app">privacy@nomsai.app</a></p>

      </div>
    </div>
  </article>

</Layout>

<style>
  .prose-legal h2 {
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: #1c1714;
    margin-top: 2.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    padding-top: 1.5rem;
    border-top: 1px solid #d4ccc4;
  }
  :global(.dark) .prose-legal h2 {
    color: white;
    border-top-color: #2a2a2a;
  }
  .prose-legal p {
    color: #6b6560;
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
  }
  :global(.dark) .prose-legal p { color: #9ca3af; }
  .prose-legal ul {
    list-style: disc;
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }
  .prose-legal li {
    color: #6b6560;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }
  :global(.dark) .prose-legal li { color: #9ca3af; }
  .prose-legal a { color: #c8920a; text-decoration: underline; }
  .prose-legal strong { color: #1c1714; }
  :global(.dark) .prose-legal strong { color: white; }
  .prose-legal code {
    background: #edeae5;
    padding: 1px 5px;
    border-radius: 4px;
    font-size: 0.88em;
    font-family: monospace;
  }
  :global(.dark) .prose-legal code { background: #1a1a1a; }
</style>
